         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25 Wilton Place ¶ London S.W. ¶ Sept. 21 1865 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ You will probably have heard by last mail of the great loss we have sustained in the death of Sir William Hooker on the 12th of last mo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.09.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M4,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Library, Royal Botanic Gardens<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25 Wilton Place</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">London S.W.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sept. 21 1865</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will probably have heard by last mail of the great loss we have sustained in the death of Sir William Hooker on the 12th of last month after an illness of three days. He was in the full enjoyment of all his faculties both of body and mind on the Tuesday preceeding and having passed his eightieth year and come to his end without suffering one cannot but feel that there is much to be thankful for. Dr Hooker having gone to sleep in a draught whilst watching his father was laid prostrate by a violent attack<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of acute rheumatism with fever,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he could not leave his bed for above a fortnight and untill last week we were very uneasy about him. He is now much better and is gone today to Buxton where the waters are celebrated for rheumatic complaints and we trust that in a few weeks more he will be able to return to Kew and take up his father's duties. In the mean time he has as yet very little use of his hands and has I believe scarcely yet been able to hold a pen. I have been out of town for the last two months and only came up for Sir William's funeral, and now again to see Dr Hooker before he left — by the end of next week I hope to be fairly at work again.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have received I believe two of your letters since I last wrote<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>—those of 25 May<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>In this edition as 65-05-25b.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and 11<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>June<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— the box per Sussex,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with supplementary Myrtaceae,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has safely arrived.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sorry that you have paid the freight. As I wrote once before<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See G. Bentham to M, 24 November 1864.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>there are great difficulties here in prepaying the boxes sent<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">from</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Establishment at Kew but none in paying the freight on boxes<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">received</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>there. It would be a great deal better for you only to pay for the boxes<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">returned</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to you and leave us to pay the freight on the boxes you send. As it is, for what is past, if you will let me know what you have paid I will myself send you the amount.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have examined the two Rubiaceae you send and ask about.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to G. Bentham, 11 June 1865.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The one (Dichostachys) is certainly a congener of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Antirrhea</hi>
               </seg>.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Antirhea</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Whether that genus ought or ought not to be united with Guettarda remains to be ascertained and it will also require further examination to ascertain whether your species is really a new one which I believe it to be. — The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>other (Woollsia) is a Lasianthus (Mephitidia Blume) very near<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>L. obscura<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">L. obscurus</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Miq. (M. obscura Bl.) if not a variety of that species which is abundant in the Archipelago and somewhat variable.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have not heard anything of the draft for £100 you mention, but it is of no consequence as it will not be strictly due to me untill next year when the 3d vol. will I hope be out.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It would be a great convenience if you were to give a systematic index to the plants described or commented on in your fragmenta and other papers, for it takes a great deal of time to hunt up the scattered notices<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>M did not publish a complete index to his own species, although B59.13.03 gave plants he had published in Victoria up to that date, and B66.13.01, pp. 217-24 contains an 'Index ordinum et generum' of the first five volumes of his<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg>. His complete censuses of all Australian genera and species were not published until the 1880s<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B82.07.05<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and supplements, B83.03.04<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and supplements, B89.12.03).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and after all there is great risk of missing some as is unavoidable with regard to the notices of Australian plants occasionally scattered in more or less obscure periodicals both here and on the Continent</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We are going to close our 2d part of the Genera<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp; Hooker (1862-83); part 2 of vol.1 was publlshed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>19 October 1865 (TL2).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with what is now printed that is to the end of Myrtaceae — Dr Hooker had Melastomaceae and all the remaining orders before Umbelliferae ready except the last revision which was not quite finished and which he will not be able to complete for many months yet and we are unwilling that what is in print should remain so long unpublished. This part will therefore be one of 300 pages only and the 3d part (to include all before Compositae) will conclude the 1st vol.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever yours sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr F. Mueller FRS</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Antirrhea</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dichostachys</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Guettarda</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Lasianthus obscura</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melastomataceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Mephitidia<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>obscurus</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Myrtaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Rubiaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Umbelliferae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Woollsia</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
